elements.title: Tomb of Aegisthus (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Tomb of Aegisthus (pictured) helped to settle the 'Helladic Heresy' over the relationship between Minoan and Mycenaean civilisation?

elements.title: Marlis Rahman (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Marlis Rahman was sworn in as Governor of West Sumatra in a garage?

elements.title: Scared (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that John Lennon believed that the Rolling Stones' 1978 hit "Miss You" was based on a sped-up version of his 1974 song "Scared"?

elements.title: Philip Wodehouse (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Philip Wodehouse spent four months chasing after HMS Peterel across the Mediterranean before catching up with the ship and taking over command from Bartholomew James?

elements.title: Lou Henry Hoover (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that American first lady Lou Henry Hoover secretly sent money to families in need during the Great Depression?

elements.title: Anon Pls. (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the novel Anon Pls. is based on the author's real-life experience going viral on Instagram?

elements.title: Iowa Colored Cowboys (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Iowa Colored Cowboys played softball for audiences of over a thousand people, in an atmosphere similar to a Harlem Globetrotters show?

elements.title: Gerald Marescaux (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Vice-Admiral Gerald Marescaux was reprimanded for wearing pyjamas?
